§I HYPOTHESIS-TO-FALSIFY
  H · cssl-rt prologue + epilogue can write magic bytes (0xC0FFEE / 0xDEADBEEF) to
       %CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH% in a way that scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh observes
       as PASS · without breaking existing T11-W19-β fs_event_jsonl pipeline

§I FAILURE-MODE-ENUMERATION (P1 · what-could-make-this-wrong)
  FM.1 · CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH unset → silent-skip · sentinel script cannot detect
         mitigation : if env-var unset · log to events.jsonl with kind=sentinel.skip
         test : sentinel_build_check.sh must exit 2 DEGRADED on env-unset (A01.4)

  FM.2 · epilogue path : panic / abort / SIGTERM / OS-kill skips epilogue
         only A01.2 says "covers normal-exit path" · panic-exit can be FM-by-design
         mitigation : write 0xDEADBEEF in atexit hook (already exists @ shutdown_hook)
         test : abnormal-exit case writes 0xC0FFEE-only · sentinel script must distinguish

  FM.3 · env-var-injection vector : malicious caller sets CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH = /etc/passwd
         consequence : we'd write magic bytes into arbitrary file
         mitigation : reject paths outside %TEMP% or pwd · diagnostic + degrade
         PD-adjacency check : N! biometric · N! consent-bypass · this is filesystem-write-arbitrary
                              which IS a sovereignty-leak shape · MUST sandbox

  FM.4 · concurrent test runs collide on same CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH
         mitigation : test harness sets per-test-PID-suffixed path

  FM.5 · TOCTOU between sentinel_build_check.sh check and process-exit
         script must read final state · not racing-during-execution

§I CHEAPEST-FALSIFICATION (cheapest test that breaks H if H is wrong)
  build a hello-world cssl program · run it with CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH=$TEMP\sentinel.bin
  inspect $TEMP\sentinel.bin :
    expect 8 bytes : 0xC0FFEE prefix + 0xDEADBEEF suffix
  if fails · either prologue or epilogue contract broken
  ⇒ ~30 LOC test · ~5 min wallclock · highest-signal-per-token

§I TOUCH-POINTS (anchored in actual codebase @ baseline dd59670)
  cssl-rt/src/loa_startup.rs    EDIT  ← prologue (after EventScope create) + epilogue (in shutdown_hook)
                                       coexist with T11-W19-β fs_event_jsonl process.start/exit
  cssl-rt/src/events.rs         EXTEND ← add sentinel.write helper if needed (or inline in loa_startup)
  scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh USE  ← read script · land golden-test against it · A01.3·A01.4
  examples/hello_main.cssl      USE   ← golden-program for sentinel-byte regression

  N! TOUCH : cssl-mir · cssl-host-* · cssl-ast (out-of-scope · pure-cssl-rt + script work)

§I ASSERT-MAPPING (boot-spec → impl-action)
  A01.1 prologue 0xC0FFEE     →  loa_startup::startup_run() · early-write before user_main
  A01.2 epilogue 0xDEADBEEF   →  loa_startup::shutdown_hook() · atexit · normal-exit path
  A01.3 script PASS=0         →  scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh on built .exe · CI green
  A01.4 script DEGRADED=2     →  exe alive but sentinel-bytes absent · transitional support

